gomodel:SYNGO_3823  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"phosphorylated ErbB2 (green; K) and ErbB4 (green; N) are present in VAChT-labeled C boutons (red; L, O); \"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n- The localization to the plasma membrane was inferred from the presumed role of Erbb4 as postsynaptic receptor for Neuregulin-1.. Experimental description: Fig.1: \" NRG1-immunopositive spots decorated the soma and proximal dendrites of large MNs at a density of 16.20 ± 2.18/100 μm of somatic perimeter (n=67 somata from P90 mice). \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3823" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

